The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Hero Honda unit to come up in Hardwar

 GARIMA SINGH

 New grounds

 Hardwar, Oct. 20: Hero Honda Motors, Indias largest two-wheeler manufacturer, and its ancillaries will invest Rs 1,900 crore in setting up a manufacturing facility at Hardwar, in the state of Uttaranchal. 

 The investment will be made over a period of the next three to four years. 

 By mid 2007, Hero Honda will invest Rs 400 crore in this new production facility, which will have an initial capacity of five lakh units. The capacity will, however, be expanded to 1.5 million units by 2010. 

 To start with, the bike manufacturer will roll out its two popular models Splendour Plus and Passion Plus. Later, the company may roll out its other models as well from this plant, said Pawan Munjal, managing director of Hero Honda Motors. 

 The two-wheeler majors premises will accommodate around 12 suppliers also. To make the supply chainstronger, the Hero Corporate Services Ltd, a unit of Hero Group, will develop two industrial parks around the upcoming facility. 

 The company has already acquired 250 acres for each park. 

 The companys plants have a total capacity to produce 3.9 million units per annum. It will increase the capacity to 4.4 million units by mid-2007 and 5.4 million units by 2010. 

 Meanwhile, arch rival Bajaj Auto has already announced setting up a manufacturing facility in Pantnagar, Uttaranchal at an investment of Rs 1,050 crore. 

 Another bike manufacturer TVS motors is also setting up its plant in neighbouring state Himachal Pradesh. 

 Facing stiff competition from Bajaj Auto, Hero Honda is planning to give its products a revamped identity. Munjal said the company is planning to give its showrooms a new look. 

 The Munjal-promoted Hero Honda will launch six more products, including variants of its existing models,by the end of this fiscal. 

 The company recently launched a new avatar CBZ CBZ X-treme in the 150cc premium segment. It is alsoplanning new offerings in the same segment by the end of the year.




